cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.CE, cs.DC, cs.GT

Reasoning: 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the implementation and performance of different energy trading mechanisms, which involves control and optimization of power systems.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper mentions the use of simulation results to compare different scenarios, which may involve the use of AI techniques.
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper discusses the benefits of local energy markets for users, which may involve computational modeling and analysis.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper focuses on distributed energy resources and local energy markets, which may involve distributed computing and communication.
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory): The paper compares scenarios where the objective of the exchange may be based on individual or social welfare, which may involve game theory concepts.
